### isOnStack() {#a47b912a3657177ec72821a3697631934}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;WebAssemblyRegStackify.cpp&#125;::TreeWalkerState::isOnStack (unsigned Reg) const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Test whether the given register is present on the stack, indicating an operand in the tree that we haven&#39;t visited yet.

Moving a definition of Reg to a point in the tree after that would change its value.

This is needed as a consequence of using implicit local.gets for uses and implicit local.sets for defs.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/webassembly/webassemblyregstackify-cpp/#l00746">746</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/webassembly/webassemblyregstackify-cpp">WebAssemblyRegStackify.cpp</a>.
